Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.61,0:01:36.03,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign: Oshiuri\NSports Station#
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.03,0:01:39.95,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Nameplate: Tegome Hiwatari#
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.76,0:01:39.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, everyone. This is Oshiuri Sports Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.73,0:01:43.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Today we have a special guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.99,0:01:48.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the grandfather of the headline-grabbing superstar of female judo, Inokuma Yawara.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.98,0:01:49.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Seventh-degree judo black belt—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.27,0:02:00.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an eight-dan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.09,0:02:02.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No young'un can beat me even today!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.47,0:02:05.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, eighth-degree black belt, Inokuma Jigoro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.84,0:02:07.65,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to say, I'm very impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.65,0:02:11.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the gold medals from both the Seoul World Cup and the World Championships.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.81,0:02:15.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,These things are just tin toys to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.61,0:02:19.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,compared to the gold medal we'll get in Barcelona next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:23.38,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Book: The Gentle Way Is Not Built in a Day\NBy Inokuma Jigoro#
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.37,0:02:27.75,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign: An eternal masterpiece! Order now and get my autograph! List price 2500 yen. Available for immediate delivery.#
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.96,0:02:22.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And speaking of impressive,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.09,0:02:27.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,the Ippon Zeoi Yawara-san pulled off against the Soviet Khrushchev in the final match...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:30.49,note,,0000,0000,0000,,TL note: His mispronunciation sounds like "exposed penis" in Japanese.#
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:30.49,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that Khuruchin girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.49,0:02:33.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she finally pulled off a good Ippon Zeoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.92,0:02:37.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing like what I've seen her do in her other matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:41.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'd rather see a Bon dance or an Awa festival than what she was doing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.99,0:02:45.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That bubbleheaded mental case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.70,0:02:48.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling a bubblehead?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:52.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of Bon dances, Kaneko and I used to go to those a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.71,0:02:54.49,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever Kaneko puts on her yukata,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.49,0:02:58.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,she's so beautiful I'd swear she's the\N reincarnation of the Goddess of Mercy herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.78,0:03:01.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, getting back to Yawara-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.24,0:03:05.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You think she compares to that Hyottoko-like girl?! {wiki: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyottoko}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.19,0:03:09.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaneko was far and away the prettier one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.13,0:03:13.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We're talking about Yawara-san, not Kaneko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.14,0:03:16.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be burning with passion as you prepare for the Barcelona Olympics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.97,0:03:21.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! The pure love Kaneko and I had for each other was very passionate!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.95,0:03:25.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But our pure passions weren't the only things burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.17,0:03:28.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when I won my first national championship,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.82,0:03:31.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted that second title so badly nobody could beat me—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.73,0:03:33.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.09,0:03:36.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Please answer my questions about Yawara-san's prospects at the Barcelona Olympics!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.88,0:03:38.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.18,0:03:43.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That word "Olympics" takes me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:03:59.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{be1\fad(250,250)\an8\pos(332,20)\shad0\3c&HFFE4F2&}April 1936
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:02.17,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign: Kyudou-kan Dojo#
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.55,0:04:08.89,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign: The monthly Inokuma Jigoro round-robin contest. Strong men welcome. Come at me however you want! {Technically "First to Five Straight Wins Contest" But I doubt Jigoro only played against five}#
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.21,0:04:09.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Next!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.49,0:04:12.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you go next!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.42,0:04:15.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My stomach's starting to hurt. I think I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.90,0:04:17.40,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign: Every Day Morning Newspaper#
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.90,0:04:17.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.89,0:04:20.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since Jigoro-kun won last year's All-Japan Judo Championship,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.75,0:04:24.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,he's become even stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.12,0:04:27.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This month's round-robin contest brought out the strongest men in the nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.42,0:04:30.37,main,,0000,0000,0000,,but they're no match for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.37,0:04:32.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Who's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.55,0:04:34.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you all lost your nerve?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:37.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.38,0:04:44.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you the one yelling like a madman?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.82,0:04:49.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I am Davis from America!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:53.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if your name is Debeso! Whaddaya want, American?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:53.77,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: Debeso means "protruding navel."#
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.20,0:05:00.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to Japan because I heard judo was the toughest form of fighting in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.28,0:05:01.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But everybody was weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.23,0:05:02.78,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Top Sign: Mumyoukishinryuu Dojo#
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.78,0:05:03.65,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Top sign: Ryuudoukan Dojo#
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:06.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are all the top dojos!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.67,0:05:09.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A foreign dojo challenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.13,0:05:14.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. If you wish to challenge me, I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.79,0:05:15.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.87,0:05:20.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone says that at the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.17,0:05:25.51,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign: Patience {I think "Perseverance" is a better translation, but it can't be helped}#
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.75,0:05:23.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.79,0:05:25.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do whatever you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.51,0:05:27.16,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.16,0:05:29.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The size difference will be too much for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.41,0:05:32.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be what those Americans eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.71,0:05:38.40,thought,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What incredible power!</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.21,0:05:43.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out! He's trying to lift you up by brute force!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.74,0:05:51.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yama Arashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.14,0:06:04.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our Jigoro-kun! He doesn't blink in the face of American power!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.66,0:06:10.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Judo can't be won by mere strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.83,0:06:13.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The flexible always commands the strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:18.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Strong! I will become your pupil!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.69,0:06:19.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Pupil?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:20.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.19,0:06:23.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You moron! You wanna be my pupil despite your puffed-up attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.44,0:06:25.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemme go, you bad-mannered galoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.78,0:06:28.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.75,0:06:30.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cuddle me with your hairy body!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.19,0:06:31.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate men!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.58,0:06:34.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I already have a fine fiancée named Kaneko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.03,0:06:36.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemme go! You wanna get thrown again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.04,0:06:39.64,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's okay, Jigoro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.53,0:06:41.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.34,0:06:48.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He came all the way from America. Let him be part of the dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.50,0:06:50.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But, Kaneko-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.94,0:06:51.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaneko?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.07,0:06:56.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wonderful, beautiful Yamato Nadeshiko! Fujiyama geisha!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.38,0:06:59.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Very happy, my new teacher! You lucky dog, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.77,0:07:03.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You Debeso bastard! I'll teach you how to be respectful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.15,0:07:06.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thought you could get away with that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.65,0:07:16.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. Davis? An American named Davis?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.61,0:07:18.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where have I heard that name before?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:20.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.85,0:07:26.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'm still on my fifth bowl here,\N but a layabout like you is on your seventh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.83,0:07:29.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, you don't know any manners!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.58,0:07:33.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Teacher, you said,\N "Appetite commands the strong."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.09,0:07:36.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! It's the flexible that commands the strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.69,0:07:42.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I can't believe that an American like you would enjoy my rice this much, Davis-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.10,0:07:44.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Your cooking is very good, Kaneko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.05,0:07:46.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It fills me with boundless, manly vigor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.82,0:07:50.32,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I told you judo isn't based on strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:54.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I was able to defeat 650 bears, then you know it takes skill!{There's a bit of Paul Bunyan in this episode...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:07:58.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I also took down giant Canadian grizzlies!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.17,0:08:00.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Those bears were just the appetizers!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.47,0:08:06.49,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The time I did an Ippon Zeoi on a man-eating whale in the Sea of Haneda was quite a feat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.33,0:08:11.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, I made its tail fin into sashimi. The marbling on it made it extra tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.88,0:08:17.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The smoked meat I made out of a mammoth I took down in Alaska was delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.47,0:08:20.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You should've had some of that, Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.42,0:08:23.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mammoths are too disgusting to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.19,0:08:27.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The eggs of the dinosaur I caught in Naruto Strait were rare delicacies!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.62,0:08:45.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaneko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:48.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is this another Great Kanto Earthquake?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:53.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaneko-san, I'm right here! Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.65,0:08:56.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Debeso?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.40,0:08:59.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.33,0:09:02.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Let's do our morning training together!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.41,0:09:10.28,thought,,0000,0000,0000,,He ain't gonna be peppy for long.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.28,0:09:12.94,thought,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't possibly keep up with my harsh training.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.94,0:09:16.61,thought,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gonna crawl back to America crying bitter tears.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.53,0:09:20.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Jigoro-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:22.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Debeso?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.63,0:09:26.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't believe who Arnold Davis is!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.64,0:09:28.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course he's unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.14,0:09:31.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That layabout eats ten bowls of rice, breaks the door lintel,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:34.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,wrecks the hallway flooring, and is a lying blowhard to boot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.48,0:09:35.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.96,0:09:39.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I found out the real story about him in my newspaper archives!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.25,0:09:42.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The real story about Debeso?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:44.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that guy you threw to the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.69,0:09:48.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,is the king of heavyweight wrestling!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.54,0:09:50.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ika rings?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.54,0:09:51.95,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: Squid rings.#
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.34,0:09:51.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrestling!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.95,0:09:55.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's like a Western style of judo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:09:59.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder he doesn't get exhausted, no matter how hard I make him work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.62,0:10:02.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He's wearing iron sandals and is doing a hundred bunny hops up and down these stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.39,0:10:06.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody else in my dojo can keep up with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.12,0:10:08.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Only that Debeso can keep up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.03,0:10:13.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Two hundred uchikomis!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:17.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Put your hips into it! Your hips!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.11,0:10:27.60,thought,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if it's wrestling or Röntgen, he's still got a lot to learn.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.88,0:10:32.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you do the 200 uchikomis?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.12,0:10:35.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, all finished! I'm starving!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.43,0:10:38.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have ten years before you can lay a paw on an Ougiya mame daifuku.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:41.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to try one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.47,0:10:43.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When you beat me, then you can have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.38,0:10:47.37,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ougiya mame daifukus are simply heavenly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.48,0:10:52.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet another thing I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.50,0:10:56.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You know something just as good as an Ougiya mame daifuku?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:10:59.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold medal! The gold medal!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.42,0:11:01.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are those as delicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.41,0:11:05.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm entering the Berlin Summer Olympics this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.63,0:11:07.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I want an Olympic gold medal!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.40,0:11:10.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Olympics? Is that a food too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.98,0:11:12.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.03,0:11:16.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Olympics is a big sports festival where the best players in the world compete.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.94,0:11:19.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you win, you become the best in the world and get a gold medal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:23.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What? The best players in the world compete?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.86,0:11:26.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I never got an invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.28,0:11:29.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't recognize judo yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.13,0:11:33.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But judo is amazing! I'm sure judo will become an Olympic sport soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.75,0:11:36.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If they don't have judo, how can anyone claim to be the best in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.74,0:11:39.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now let's go do some randori!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.01,0:11:42.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Who needs the Olympics? Who needs gold medals?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.61,0:12:46.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it fits you, Davis-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.10,0:12:50.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, a yukata! Wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.12,0:12:52.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a good bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:56.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, Kaneko-san, let's go see the fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.08,0:12:57.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness. It fits perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.10,0:13:01.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice! Very good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:02.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Debeso! Time to see the fireworks—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.95,0:13:06.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Kaneko! Very, very thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.31,0:13:15.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,200)}You're banished!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.03,0:13:30.95,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign: Kyudou-kan Dojo#
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.33,0:13:30.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Jigoro-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.95,0:13:34.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When foreigners kiss like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.08,0:13:36.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,they're just showing their deep, platonic affection for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.86,0:13:37.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.60,0:13:39.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That Debeso bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.98,0:13:42.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He kissed my fiancée even though I've never kissed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.99,0:13:43.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forgive him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.84,0:13:46.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Next!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.49,0:14:04.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been practicing here all alone ever since that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.56,0:14:07.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't listen to reason, and neither will Jigoro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.97,0:14:20.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since Davis-san left,\N our house has felt really empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.04,0:14:27.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm relieved because I don't have to deal with that royal pain anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.27,0:14:45.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad news!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.32,0:14:48.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad news! Jigoro-kun, this is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.73,0:14:51.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with all the noise?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.16,0:14:56.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Davis-san is by the river, fighting the guys from the Ryuudoukan and Mumyoukishinryuu dojos!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.70,0:14:58.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.75,0:15:04.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Debeso!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.80,0:15:05.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He's nuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.90,0:15:09.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Debeso can't win if he's outnumbered!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.10,0:15:15.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Debeso! Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.81,0:15:16.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Debe—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.21,0:15:24.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:26.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Debeso.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.76,0:15:32.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so damn proud over beating a bunch of weaklings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.15,0:15:38.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I tossed 2,000 Imagawa soldiers in a row when I trained in Okehazama.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.15,0:15:38.75,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: He's referencing a battle during the Sengoku Period (1467-1600).#
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.75,0:15:43.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Well, I took out an army of 5,000 Indians in Mexico!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.75,0:15:45.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all you did?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.50,0:15:48.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when I secluded myself in the mountains of Hidatakayama,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.02,0:15:51.76,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I tossed 10,000 abominable snowmen all the way to the moon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.20,0:15:58.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Back in Arizona, I threw 20,000 aliens and their UFOs back to Mars where they came from!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.87,0:16:04.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving Japan tomorrow to go to the Berlin Olympics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.98,0:16:06.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is where we say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.29,0:16:11.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Who gives a damn about Berlin or its Olympics?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.59,0:16:13.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do your horseplay over there for all I care!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.63,0:16:14.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Jigoro-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.73,0:16:17.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, let's have a match before you go off to your little festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.66,0:16:18.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A match?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.44,0:16:25.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be a pupil against his "teechur." It'll be a serious, man-to-man fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:27.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be playing for mame daifukus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.58,0:16:30.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Jigoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.18,0:16:33.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.18,0:16:35.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Come at me any way you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.45,0:16:40.79,thought,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your guard down, Jigoro-kun.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.79,0:16:43.06,thought,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not the old Davis you're facing.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.41,0:17:05.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My God! Such intensity!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.79,0:17:08.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,They've been fighting for almost three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.81,0:17:10.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Debeso?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.94,0:17:12.16,main,,0000,0000,0000,,All you've been doing is shouting!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.16,0:17:14.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the power that brought down a mammoth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.98,0:17:20.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the strength you used to do an Ippon Zeoi on a whale, Jigoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.43,0:17:23.32,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Whales are just kappa farts!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.32,0:17:27.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was training in Nara, I pulled an Osoto Gari on the Great Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.14,0:17:29.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,and an Okuri Eri Jime on the Five-Storied Pagoda!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.73,0:17:35.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when I was training in New York, I felled the Empire State Building
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.69,0:17:37.70,main,,0000,0000,0000,,and made the Statue of Liberty cry uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.09,0:17:53.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! Get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.30,0:18:00.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:03.52,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That ain't nothing, Debeso!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.52,0:18:06.52,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a much harder time bringing down Mt. Fuji!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.23,0:18:10.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This fight's not over!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.26,0:18:14.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when I defeated Niagara Falls,\N it was a total come-from-behind victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.90,0:18:17.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Davis, give up! Your arm will get busted!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.90,0:18:21.87,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit being stubborn and give up, Debeso!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.14,0:18:26.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This ain't over by a long shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.58,0:18:27.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Davis?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.13,0:18:32.92,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It ends here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.05,0:18:34.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:37.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know who won! Let's fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.87,0:18:42.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be in any festive mood if your arm's all bandaged up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.46,0:18:43.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now get going to your Olympics!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.72,0:18:50.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you're still not getting any Ougiya mame daifukus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.95,0:18:53.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Jigoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.63,0:19:01.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,One day... One of these days we'll play judo in the Olympics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.57,0:19:06.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When that happens, we'll have our judo match! I promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.29,0:19:09.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Good! We'll see whether I take the gold medal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.66,0:19:13.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,or if you get to eat mame daifukus!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.56,0:19:27.52,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\pos(568,185)\c&H837C6C&}Ice
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.56,0:19:27.52,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Maehata! Go, Maehata!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.52,0:19:29.71,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,Maehata, go, go, go! Go, Maehata!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.71,0:19:31.52,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,Maehata's fast! She's got the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:33.74,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, go, go, go! Go, Maehata!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.74,0:19:36.37,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,Maehata Hideko wins! She won! She won!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.37,0:19:40.24,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,She did it! She becomes the first Japanese woman to win a gold medal in swimming!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.24,0:19:44.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Banzai! Banzai! Banzai!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.15,0:19:47.20,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the 11th Olympiad in Berlin. We will now announce the results of the other events.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.20,0:19:49.60,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,In the heavyweight freestyle wrestling championship match,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.60,0:19:52.43,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,we had the American Davis vs. Palusalu of Estonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.43,0:19:56.29,announcer,,0000,0000,0000,,The Estonian Palusalu won the match on a judge's decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:01.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Debeso lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.48,0:20:03.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He fought me to a draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.53,0:20:06.85,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've tossed more than a hundred good athletes, but he still lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.85,0:20:12.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You see? Some incredibly talented people compete at the Olympics.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.73,0:20:14.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.09,0:20:16.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Horse hockey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.46,0:20:18.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Who gives a damn about the Olympics or the gold medal?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.75,0:20:21.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Without judo, how can you tell who's the best in the world?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.79,0:20:26.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran. And I kept running, and running, and running.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.77,0:20:35.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, I threw that giant Estonian way up into the Berlin skies
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.71,0:20:39.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,and put the world in a state of shock!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.21,0:20:45.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The cheers and applause I received lasted more than three days and three nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.14,0:20:51.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Jigoro is number one! Jigoro is number one!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.99,0:20:53.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of my brilliant achievement, judo became an Olympic sport,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:57.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,and they decided to hold the next Olympics in Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.91,0:21:04.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're obviously lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.22,0:21:05.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You saying I'm lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:09.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't have run all the way to Berlin!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.97,0:21:12.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Berlin was closer in those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.63,0:21:15.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,However, despite my efforts,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.05,0:21:20.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,the 1940 Tokyo Olympics were canceled two years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.36,0:21:24.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Second Sino-Japanese War had turned into a quagmire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:26.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Life was getting uglier and more militaristic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.80,0:21:26.30,note,,0000,0000,0000,,Headlines: Imperial Declaration of War\NWestern Pacific Battles Begin#
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.30,0:21:30.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, we plunged ourselves into that disastrous war.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.41,0:21:37.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no Olympics for thirteen years after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.36,0:21:44.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,so I wasn't able to keep my promise to Debeso to fight him on the world stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.00,0:21:52.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But the amazing judo skills I displayed in Berlin became the talk of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.53,0:21:56.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,and in 1964 the Olympics were finally held in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.71,0:22:03.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Judo became an Olympic sport,\N and it spread throughout the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.57,0:22:08.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So the fact that there is judo today is all thanks to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.50,0:22:11.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I already heard that on TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.03,0:22:13.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, how much of it is true anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.89,0:22:16.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,At least you've matured into a real wisenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.19,0:22:18.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you boiled the grime from under my fingernails and drank it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.88,0:22:23.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,you'd be able to win one, maybe two gold medals in Barcelona! {apparently a saying that means, "If you tried to act a little more like me..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.47,0:22:25.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather die than drink that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.94,0:22:29.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, the tea is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.35,0:22:31.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I also have Grandpa's favorite—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.61,0:22:34.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we have here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.45,0:22:40.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I really wanted Debeso to eat these.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.76,0:22:47.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ougiya mame daifukus, even if they've become much smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.10,0:22:57.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yawara.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.93,0:23:02.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,After watching my moving story, you're all fired up to get that gold medal, ain'tcha?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.74,0:23:03.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.80,0:23:05.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, I know what you're trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.14,0:23:07.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's 'cause I'm the one who knows you best.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.66,0:23:08.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know me at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.62,0:23:12.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to work for Tsurukame Travel!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.22,0:23:14.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You still trying that runaround on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.13,0:23:16.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You know I ain't gonna allow that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.48,0:23:17.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yawara!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.31,0:23:19.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Up, The Graduation Match!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.79,0:23:24.84,nextEp,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(30,0)\bord0.7\b1\be1\fs24\fscy100\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HCBD9EA&\pos(467,260)}Next Up, The Graduation Match!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.74,0:23:22.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be getting my Harai Goshi if you miss this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:24.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,
